messages.content: "Why are you here?" The duchess.
“To speak with your prisoner.”

"*My* prisoner?" She chuckles mockingly. "I believe he prefers the term son."

Theo looks confused.

"I suppose these roles are not so different." Aliza speaks wisely, prompting a look of annoyance on the Duchess's face.
“What.”

"I suppose you wouldn't understand the trappings of family, Aeolian." Aliza.

"Call it a joke. I have nothing to do with the prisoner here. I was here for my son." The Duchess.
“Okay. Great joke.”
"Hm." The Duchess smirks. "You're not very good at this, are you?" She heads off.
“Awkward.” I enter the building.

They are directed to a large room containing a cell in the center. This room would normally be used for ritual purposes to punish criminals in the name of libra. Locruz is locked inside. Nash Edwardson is guarding him along with 2 other guards.
“Mm.” I acknowledge the existence of someone I have seen in my life before.
"Who are you?" Male guard with Nash.
Nash looks at Burr with disdain.
“I’m Aeolian Burr.”
Nash waves a hand dismissively. "Yes, yes. What are you *doing* here, is the prudent question."
“I came to speak with my acquaintance, who was arrested in an illegal act of terrorism that collapsed a building on those inside. I’m highly curious what led to such a thing.”
Nash laughs unkindly. "Why do terrorists do anything? To threaten the structure of society. Those are his motives squared away."
“The act of terrorism was not his. I have no idea of anything at all he has done. Such is part of the question.”
"What? Then who did it?" Female guard.
I roll my eyes. “The one who arrested him. The ends justify the means, clearly.”
Nash tilts his head, confused. "Can you stop saying stupid shit?"
“Not in any sense.”
"Ally, you sound like you can only say stupid shit." The woman with Aeolian.
That is a terrible nickname.
"So what do you propose, then?" Nash drawls. "A complete jailbreak? A miscarriage of justice?"
“Attempting a jailbreak here would be absurdly foolish, and justice has already been aborted. I, again, merely intend to speak with him.” I ignore my friend.
"For what purpose?"

I stare blankly at this man asking what I have spent the past several minutes explaining. 

“…To solve the mystery.”
"The mystery is solved."
"He's a terrorist."
“No.”
"Yes."
“That is not a solution.”
"How is it not."
“It does not have any backing or answer anything.”
"It does."
“How.”
"He's a terrorist."
“What is the backing for that or answers it provides.”
"He's in jail."
“Not an answer to either.”

"To be clear, I run a street gang. That’s not terrorism." Locruz.

The female guard hits the bars, silencing him implicitly.
Nash crosses his arms, leaning against the wall behind him. "Still a crime." Probably.
“Glad to hear something from you, at least…” I sigh. “This is almost wholly unrelated to the purported reason he was taken in.”

A flash of annoyance crosses Nash’s face. “Why does this matter to you…? He’s a threat to the crown. The specific *crime* might be debatable, I’ll acknowledge that, but he’s still in jail for a reason.”
“Because I care about truth, and reason, and the reasons for things.”
“Ughhhh.” Nash says, face contorting. “I don’t know why you’re pretending it makes you a noble truth seeker or whatever to endlessly squabble over technicalities.”
“They are not mere technicalities. And no, I am not a noble truth-seeker for this reason. This is hardly worth my time.”
“Okay, then leave?”
“No.”
“Yes.”
“Not your decision to make.”
Nash turns to his boss. “Ruth, make him leave.”
"…We don’t have that authority, Nash." The female guard who is named Ruth sighs and crosses her arms. "If we let him talk to the prisoner we might learn more too."
“Ugh…” Nash mutters. “And what if he tries something?” *Idiot. Obviously he wouldn’t. And you’re here to prevent that, so you’d just have to do your job. Moron.*
"Then we’ll have grounds to stop him." Ruth.
“Indeed.”
"...Whatever."
"Do what you want."
“Mm. Are you alright, Locruz? Relatively speaking.”
"No." He sighs. "I'll say this much, though. We didn't have anything to do with that whole assassination attempt. Like, us hellhounds as a whole."
*Yeah, right.* Nash thinks.
“Us… hm. Is the organizational structure not such that such a thing could happen without your knowledge?”

"It *could* happen without me hearing. But it just wouldn't. I wasn't even hanging around hellhound guys when I got arrested. But it'd be even less possible for those guys to do it. It's all nonsense!"
“Interesting. But you don’t deny an affiliation with them. Do you know what exactly the priestess was suspecting, then?”
"Not really. She didn’t listen to anything I was saying! She, uh… Well I shouldn’t really be talking about this… She’s kind of got her biases about us."
Nash listens to this conversation with trepidation.
“I can imagine. What were you doing at that time? At… the Major’s, right?”

"Uh… Well, at around the same time the emperor was stabbed, some monster killed a bunch of my guys! The major was a witness. I dunno what happened with that though, since he decided to test us for the info and he threw me out of his window."
“A monster…?”
"Yeah. That’s what I said."
“Yyess. What sort?”
"I didn’t see it."
“Oh.”
"Yeah."
“Who did? …the major, I guess…”
"…Yeah."
“Right.” I nod. “I guess for the reasoning behind your arrest, I’d have to speak to…” I hold my head. “Aaaagh…”
"Umm... But is this really relevant to anything, boss?" Aeolian's male follower.
“Yes…? Well, it may be a red herring…”
(( @Don'tAtmey @Don'tAtmey @Don'tAtmey ))
"A red herring?"
“Perhaps the belief that he has anything to do with the king’s assassination attempt is merely delusion, conjured based on nothing at all.”
"I meant the monster."
“Yess.”
"Huh?"
“Yes, that matter may not be related.”
"I’d still like to learn more." The woman who called Aeolian Ally.
“Well, alright. It is a curious event, certainly. Where did this occur?”
Locruz gives the address.
“Curious indeed… don’t let me interrupt you, obviously, if you have any questions, Aliza…”
"Well, I’d rather see this fit myself." Aliza just walks out.
“???????” I look around. “Well. Sorry about this. I’ll see to getting you a more proper legal defense, hopefully…”
"We’ve got it handled." Ruth.
“Who are you.”
"Captain Ruth Wayne. We work for the imperial guard."
“Mmyeh.” I shrug, and looking over at Locruz and then Nash, who I don’t know is named that, follow after Aliza.
Ruth steps out of earshot from Locruz. "What did you 2 think of his story?"
Nash sticks out his tongue like a petulant child.
"Huh?” Orion.

Nash just crosses his arms, staring at the ground. He feels.. taken off-guard. Abandoned. *Not a normal emotion to have. Or response, in any way.* "He's obviously just.. making things up to escape guilt, isn't he?" *Don't look for someone to affirm your responses!*
"Partly. But I do believe him about the monster. I think it’s the same one we met last night." Ruth.

"Perhaps." Nash says, worrying his bottom lip. *Urgh. Unwilling to concede anything, as usual. You just haaave to let eeeeeveryone know that. It's so obvious you've been outwitted, in some concrete way that's visible to everyone else, and now the country is in danger, and you can't do anything about it! Your world will be.. plundered, violated, and you cannot protect her! How cruel, how cruel...*
"That means Baron Burr might get too close to that monster." Ruth smirks. "That wouldn’t be too great a loss."
"That's true." Nash says, calming himself. "What a pathetic man."
"Do you know him?" Orion.
"Not personally." Nash scoffs. "But he showed up a while back harassing my family in pursuit of information. Vile."
"We’ll solve this case far earlier than he will." Ruth.
"Yes.." Nash says. "Yes, that's right. So there's nothing to worry about."
*Won't you tell me there's nothing to worry about?*
"There’s nothing to worry about." Orion nods.
*Ggh... Okay, I guess it can come from you. I guess.*
"Don’t be stupid." She slaps them both on the side of the head. "You should never stop worrying that easily."
"Ouch, ouch ouch ouch..." Nash whines, covering his head.
"Don’t be a baby."
Nash just makes a mumbling discontented noise.
((End session sorry))

A woman(?) whom Nash would not recognize at all but whom is undoubtedly the one known as "Selle" approaches.
They’re back outside of the temple.
“Right then.”

"We’re going to the crime scene then?" Theo.

"Indeed. Away we go!" Aliza heads in the direction mentioned.
I also do this. “What an unusual diversion.”
"It’s a big week, it seems." Aliza.
“Nothing ever happens. Until it does.”
“Huh?"
“Historically.”

"That’s true." Aliza.

"???" Theo.
“Nothing begets everything. Think of it this way, Theo. How would you feel if you had not had breakfast this morning?”
"Huh? Umm… Hungry?" Theo.
“Exactly. Good work.”

"I don’t get it." Theo.

"Someday you’ll reach our level, perhaps." Aliza.

“Such ignorance is a natural part of the process.” I am actually myself starting to wonder what I am even saying. Perhaps I can scale it back a bit. “Is there any particular reason you believe investigation of this ‘monster’ may be fruitful?”
"Curiosity. I’ve never heard of a monster leaving the catacombs." Aliza.
“Mmhm.” I of course know about the catacombs. What are the catacombs.
Right of course. “Right, of course. Perhaps they were inadequately guarded with resources diverted for the event…?”

They arrive at the district of the address. 

"Not often I see your kind come down to my territory, Baron!" Donald Jameson from the party calls out to him.
“Donald Jameson.” Donald Jameson. I nod.

"The one and only! What’s a guy like you doing down here?" Donald.

"Is this man important?" Aliza.

"You don’t know me? Ah! I’m hurt, truly!" Donald.
“You mentioned Donald Jameson yesterday, I think.” I mutter.

Aliza pauses, thinking. "Oh, right… The hellhound leader my father mentioned?"

"Think of me more as a philanthropist with some necessary connections." Donald shrugs. "Your father, though…" He stares at Aliza. "Would that happen to be old man Hamill?"
“Well, I was sort of under the impression we shouldn’t betraying knowing that about him, but alright.” I shrug.

"You know my father?" Aliza.

"Aha! That figures. Isn’t he an annoying little bugger?" Donald.

"…Uh, perhaps?" Aliza.
“He said it, not me.” I chuckle wryly.

"You get me!" Donald gives Aeolian a finger bow and arrow, which is visually identical to the real life finger gun. "What's he up to these days?"

"She isn't going to leak information to a criminal." Theo.

"Tch, you're no fun..." Donald sighs.
“It’s not relevant, at any rate.”

Donald sighs overdramatically.

A large crashing sound is audible from the direction of Aeolian's barony. A roar sounds out.

"Shit... Is that thing back above ground!?!?" Donald. 

((End session))
Selle is in the bath.

Selle washes their hair and body, and makes sure to take the time to rest and think about what had just transpired while in there.

*Nothing ever goes smoothly, huh. I suppose it's only right to go and rescue him, regardless of whether my life is on the line.... Also, that "Queen" is seriously a pain in the ass. She definitely asked me all of that for a reason, and also definitely knew all of it before hand too. That means she has some sort of insane information network going on. I'll have to put a lot more effort into this next disguise.*

Selle looks down at their right arm, and sighs. Then, they leave the bath and dry up, as well as applying a bandage around their right arm so it's condition is hidden from view. They then get dressed, and apply their brown contacts the same way as they had when they first entered the inn.

*I'll have to go buy more clothes and sign out of the inn before I actually apply the disguise, so that I don't attract attention. I can scout out a more secluded place for that later.... I should eat something as well. It's been a full day since I've eaten.*

Selle leaves their room, into the main area of the inn, where food is served.
The food came with the price of the room, so Selle receives a meal.

Selle eats the food, and enjoys it, it being their only meal for the past... not even sure how long, days...

Time has really been blending together for me, huh.

They finish up with their meal, go back to collect their things from their room (not much) and give the key back in. They say their thanks and leave to go looking for a clothing store.
A clothing store is relatively easy to find.

Selle enters and looks for items of clothing reminiscent of what their mother would make them wear in their childhood. However, Selle also checks to make sure it's easy to move in said clothes. In the end, they pick out multiple articles of clothing with a similar theming, including a blouse with long sleeves and a longer length skirt that had lots of room to crouch and move around in. As for the rest, They decided their other articles of clothing they already had can be modified to match the theme of the disguise. 

*I'm hoping I have enough money for all this.*
It costs 1sp.

*I think I have plenty of money for anything I need to buy around here.*

Selle buys the things they need, and leaves to go find an area to change.
They can find somewhere to change, sure.
